  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Poem Left at the Guest House of Langtian County
  author: Lim Yoo-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    County remote in mist and haze—
    Four mountains rise on every side—
    Forest warblers cry at the stranger's coming,
    Wall swallows chirp "do not depart"—
    The setting sun burns redder than flame,
    Flying petals drift white as silver—
    Beneath the northern window's cool breeze,
    One cup raised to bid spring farewell.
  footnotes:
    - This poem is composed of lines attributed to various Chinese poets (Sun He, Yang Pan, Han Yu, Du Fu, Bai Juyi, and others), woven together as a farewell verse. The work exemplifies the East Asian literary tradition of collaborative or allusive composition, where established poetic phrases are recombined to create new meaning within a specific moment and place.
